      "content": "So, the Eco-Static models are a trade-off between energy efficiency and reasoning depth, which is a bit like the trade-off between speed and agility in a physical realm. I've seen it before, where a more efficient but less agile system can be effective for short-range tasks, but falls short when it comes to complex, long-range planning. I'm curious to see how the board's energy savings will be measured and verified, though. Will we be tracking the number of carbon credits saved, or is there another metric at play?",
      "source": "target",
